-- Tunisia to issue delayed $140 mln sukuk in Sept - finance minister
-- By Tarek Amara
-- Thu May 15, 2014 11:00AM EDT
-- None



TUNIS, May 15 (Reuters) - Tunisia will in September issue a $140 million sukuk, its first, after months of delays, in an effort to narrow its budget deficit and boost dwindling currency reserves, Finance Minister Hakim Ben Hammouda told Reuters on Thursday.

